remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKWebpEncoder` can encode both still images and animated WebP files. Use the
`Encode` overloads for single images, and `EncodeAnimated` for multi-frame
animations.

This is a static utility class and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
// Encode a bitmap as a still WebP image
using var bitmap = new SKBitmap(200, 200);
var options = SKWebpEncoderOptions.Default;
using var data = SKWebpEncoder.Encode(bitmap.PeekPixels(), options);
File.WriteAllBytes("image.webp", data.ToArray());
```
